        <num>CCP 3396.14</num>
        <heading>3396.14.  Security of independent administrator</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3396.14.  Security of independent administrator
Except where the testament provides otherwise, an independent administrator shall not be required to provide security for the administration of the estate.  If an interested person, such as an heir, legatee, or creditor of the estate requests security, then upon application by such party, and after a contradictory hearing, the court may order the independent administrator to furnish security as the court determines to be adequate.</p>
        </content>
